						               													<description>In alternate Malaysia, Gila Bola takes players in a time where football is all the craze!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Being put into the shoes of a captain in a football Fanclub of your Favourite Team, you are going around the country stadium to stadium to strategically manipulate game's result as your Backup Team is victorious, whilst Rival Team is driven to the bottom of the League.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player will do 1 main action : move their standee (by spending their Fuel) to any of the tiles that represent an ongoing match in the round and secretly(face down) playing a Match card that will manipulate the outcome of the match. A free/optional action they can do is to change their resources: discard 2 Match cards to draw 1 new Match card, discard 2 Match cards to get 1 Fuel or Use 1 Fuel to draw 1 new Match card. Once one of the tile are filled with 4 cards, the rest of the player who haven't played their turn will do so and all 8 matches results will revealed. Winning, losing or draw, all the points will be added to the league tables using football league rules (3pt for winner, 1pt for draw, 0 for the losing) and also adding/deducting goal differences.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All player have 1 Favourite team that is public information, but their backup &amp;amp; rival team are secret so they need to be very discreet and manipulate the matches in their favour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played in 3 rounds. At the end of the game, all player will reveal 3 of their teams and depend on that team standings, the player with the most points win!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
